+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JhBtBETnVtUyJQfg3Er8bC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n     2→\n     3→Implement the core of the task queue: the ability to add tasks and retrieve them in first-in, first-out order.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- The queue should accept a payload (any data) when a task is added, and return a task object.\n     8→- Each task must have a unique identifier (e.g., UUID), a status, and a creation timestamp.\n     9→- New tasks start in a \"pending\" state.\n    10→- Retrieving the next task should return the oldest pending task and transition it to a \"processing\" state.\n    11→- If no tasks are available, retrieval should return `null`.\n    12→- There should be a way to check how many tasks are waiting.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SDJbjXBWTdSiP4y4YTpxKA","session_id":"5e89c2d1-8af7-43e3-aba0-7a2329afe11b","uuid":"64848036-073f-40b9-b457-9a7bbd0019ec"}
