+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tbx1PtNtaTxQ7GcbmafH7B","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n     2→\n     3→Add a dead letter queue (DLQ) to capture tasks that have permanently failed after exhausting all retries.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- When a task has no more retries left, it is automatically moved to a dead letter queue associated with its original queue.\n     8→- There should be a way to view all dead-lettered tasks for a given queue.\n     9→- Dead-lettered tasks should retain their error information and a count of how many times they failed.\n    10→- It should be possible to move a dead-lettered task back to its original queue for a fresh round of retries.\n    11→- There should be a way to clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue.\n    12→- Each named queue has its own independent dead letter queue.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SDJbjXBWTdSiP4y4YTpxKA","session_id":"5e89c2d1-8af7-43e3-aba0-7a2329afe11b","uuid":"3f545e92-8912-4ac8-b61c-a666825359c6"}
