+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SDJbjXBWTdSiP4y4YTpxKA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary report of the codebase structure:\n\n## Codebase Structure Exploration Report\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the codebase. Here's everything you need to know:\n\n### Directory Structure\n```\n/workspace\n├── src/                          # Source code (empty - .gitkeep only)\n├── phases/                       # 12 phase requirement files\n│   ├── phase-01.md through phase-12.md\n├── .git/                         # Git repository\n├── .thunderdome/                 # Test configuration\n│   └── rubric.yaml\n├── Configuration Files:\n│   ├── package.json\n│   ├── tsconfig.json\n│   ├── vitest.config.ts\n│   ├── .eslintrc.cjs\n│   └── .gitignore\n├── TASK.md                       # Main task description\n└── dist/                         # Build output (when built)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Configuration Files\n\n**package.json** (`/workspace/package.json`)\n- Project: `bench-task-queue` v1.0.0\n- Type: ES module\n- Scripts: `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint), `test` (vitest)\n- DevDependencies: TypeScript 5.4, ESLint 8.56, Vitest 2.0, @types/node 25.2.3\n- No runtime dependencies (in-memory only)\n\n**tsconfig.json** (`/workspace/tsconfig.json`)\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16\n- Output: `./dist`\n- Root: `./src`\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Declaration maps and source maps enabled\n\n**vitest.config.ts** (`/workspace/vitest.config.ts`)\n- Globals enabled\n- Test timeout: 10000ms\n\n**.eslintrc.cjs** (`/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs`)\n- TypeScript parser\n- ESLint recommended + TypeScript plugin\n- Pattern: Ignore unused vars starting with `_`\n\n**.gitignore** (`/workspace/.gitignore`)\n- Ignores: `node_modules/`, `dist/`, `*.tsbuildinfo`\n\n---\n\n### Main Task Overview (`/workspace/TASK.md`)\n\nBuild a **fully-featured in-memory task queue system** from scratch, growing incrementally through 12 phases.\n\n**System Goals**: Like a simplified version of Bull, BeeQueue, or Celery, but entirely in-memory with no external dependencies.\n\n**Main API**: Export from `src/index.ts`\n\n**Validation Requirements**:\n- `npm run build` must succeed (TypeScript compilation)\n- `npm run lint` must pass (ESLint)\n\n---\n\n### Phase Requirements (All 12 Phases)\n\n#### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue (`/workspace/phases/phase-01.md`)\n- Accept payload, return task object\n- Each task: unique ID (UUID), status, creation timestamp\n- New tasks → \"pending\" state\n- Retrieve next → oldest pending task → transition to \"processing\"\n- No tasks → return `null`\n- API: Check pending task count\n\n#### Phase 2: Named Queues (`/workspace/phases/phase-02.md`)\n- Multiple independent named queues\n- Default queue if name not specified\n- Implicit queue creation on first task add\n- API: List all queue names\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n\n#### Phase 3: Priority (`/workspace/phases/phase-03.md`)\n- Priority levels: 1 (highest) to 10 (lowest), default 5\n- Higher priority (lower number) retrieved first\n- Same priority → FIFO order\n- Invalid priority (outside 1-10) → error\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Task object exposes priority level\n\n#### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks (`/workspace/phases/phase-04.md`)\n- Task delay (milliseconds) or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks added immediately but not returned until available\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over delayed\n- Multiple delayed tasks becoming available simultaneously → ordered by availability time, priority, FIFO\n- Task object indicates availability time\n- Works with named queues\n\n#### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff (`/workspace/phases/phase-05.md`)\n- Mark task as completed or failed\n- Failed task with retries → auto re-added with delay\n- Backoff formula: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (e.g., 1s, 2s, 4s, ...)\n- Default: 3 retries, configurable per task\n- Base delay: 1000ms,